{
  "texts": [
    "(i) Data Annotation: Creating high quality annotated dataset in Indian Languages are the biggest challenges for NER.",
    "(ii) Language Diversity: Developing NER models for Indian Languages requires specialized expertise in each Languages.",
    "Labelled dataset for NER in Indian Languages is often scarce.",
    "This scarcity hinders the training of an accurate NER models.Input • Code Mixing • Transliterated Output • Diverse Entity Type • Ambiguty Usages • Low-Resource Language • Domain Specify Methodology • Data Annotation • Language Diversity • Evaluation Metrics(iii) Evaluation Metrics: Standard Evaluation metric may not capture the of NER in Indian Languages.",
    "Additionally, Adapting NER models trained on one Indian Languages to another can be challenging due to linguistic differences for cross lingual transfer.Based on the previously mentioned issues and difficulties, we have discovered that building an effective model requires a strong understanding of how to combine the various elements, as well as expertise in both machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL)."
  ]
